----------------------------------------------------------------
💡 Rule vs ViolationRule (Full Detail – SailPoint):-
🔹 1️⃣ Rule kya hota hai?

👉 Rule = Reusable Java-based logic block
Ye SailPoint ka core concept hai jahan tum custom logic likhte ho

🔧 Rule kaha use hota hai?
Identity creation/update
Provisioning (account create/delete)
Approval flow
Attribute transformation
Connector logic

📦 Internally kya hota hai?
Rule ek XML object hota hai
Uske andar Java code hota hai
SailPoint runtime pe execute karta hai

🧠 Real Example:-
<Rule name="CheckDepartmentRule" type="Identity">
    <Source>
        if(identity.getDepartment().equals("IT")) {
            return true;
        }
        return false;
    </Source>
</Rule>
🔍 Samajh:-
👉 Ye rule bas ek condition check kar raha hai,
👉 Koi violation ya risk detect nahi kar raha.

🔹 2️⃣ ViolationRule kya hota hai?
👉 ViolationRule = Special type ka Rule jo Policy violation detect karta hai,
Ye normal rule nahi hai — ye specifically Policy Engine ke saath use hota hai.

🔧 Ye kaha use hota hai?
Policy check ke time
SoD (Segregation of Duties)
Compliance validation
Access certification

📦 Internally kya hota hai?
Ye bhi XML + Java hota hai
Lekin output me Violation object / message deta hai
Policy system ko batata hai: "problem hai"

🧠 Real Example:-
<Rule name="SoDViolationRule" type="Violation">
    <Source>
        if(identity.hasRole("Admin") && identity.hasRole("Auditor")) {
            return "Violation: Admin + Auditor not allowed";
        }
        return null;
    </Source>
</Rule>
🔍 Samajh:-
👉 Ye rule risk detect kar raha hai
👉 Agar condition true → violation generate
👉 Agar false → koi issue nahi.

🔸 Execution Level difference:-
Point	              Rule	                      ViolationRule
Execution-----------Har jagah----------------Sirf Policy evaluation me
Trigger-------------Developer call/config----Policy engine automatically
Context-------------Flexible-----------------------Policy context

🔸 Output Difference:-
Rule Output	            ViolationRule Output
boolean------------------Violation message
object-------------------Risk / violation
modified data------------compliance issue

🔸 Real Life Mapping:-
🔹 Rule (Normal Logic):-
👉 "User IT department me hai ya nahi?"

🔹 ViolationRule (Security Logic):-
👉 "User ke paas dangerous combination access hai ya nahi?"

👉 Rule = "Kya karna hai" define karta hai
👉 ViolationRule = "Kya galat ho raha hai" detect karta hai.

()Ek hi Rule engine hota hai:-
Usme different types hote hain:-
Identity Rule
Provisioning Rule
Approval Rule
Violation Rule
